<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take one’s orders • take orders</xh5><p> <i>take one’s orders</i>—receive directions or commands: The civil patrol serves under the command of the chief commissioner, who <u>takes his orders</u> from the army command.</p><p> <i>take orders—</i>1. <i>= take one’s orders:</i> Jules had to <u>take orders</u> from him pretending to go along with him in his ridiculous schemes. 2. <i>(also: take holy orders)</i> become a priest in the Anglican Church: I had scarcely <u>taken orders</u> a year before I began to think seriously of matrimony.</p> </entry>
